lank%5C%22%3EDorset%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20almost%20seven%20feet%20long.%20It%20belonged%20to%20a%20pliosaur%2C%20an%20extinct%20marine%20reptile%20that%20terrorized%20the%20oceans%20from%20the%20earliest%20Jurassic%20to%20early%20Late%20Cretaceous%20periods%2C%20approximately%20150%20million%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ancient%20pliosaur%20was%20the%20%26quot%3Bultimate%20killing%20machine%2C%26quot%3B%20able%20to%20navigate%20the%20ocean%20at%20high%20speed%20and%20kill%20its%20prey%20with%20a%20single%20bite%2C%20per%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20skull%20has%20130%20long%20and%20razor-sharp%20teeth.%20Each%20tooth%20has%20fine%20ridges%20at%20the%20back%20to%20pierce%20its%20prey's%20flesh%2C%20quickly%20extract%2C%20and%20prepare%20itself%20for%20a%20swift%20second%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20prey%20was%20dolphin-like%20creatures%20and%20other%20pliosaurs%2C%20scientists%20told%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPliosaurs%20had%20jaws%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fbite-strength-analysis-tyrannosaurus-rex-dinosaur-2017-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwice%20as%20powerful%20as%20today's%20saltwater%20crocodiles%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20animal%20would%20have%20been%20so%20massive%20that%20I%20think%20it%20would%20have%20been%20able%20to%20prey%20effectively%20on%20anything%20that%20was%20unfortunate%20enough%20to%20be%20in%20its%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20Andre%20Rowe%2C%20a%20palaeobiologist%20from%20Bristol%20University%2C%20told%20BBC%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20creatures%20measured%2032-39%20feet%20long%2C%20propelling%20themselves%20quickly%20with%20four%20powerful%20flipper-like%20limbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20no%20doubt%20that%20this%20was%20sort%20of%20like%20an%20underwater%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fover-a-billion-t-rexes-lived-on-earth-where-are-the-bones-2023-5%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ET.%20Rex%3C%2Fa%3