to%20be%20sold%20before%20they%20are%20removed%20from%20display.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223935%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Costco%20rotisserie%20chickens%20are%20time%20stamped.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6571f4e858e7c0c29a2aa70a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222828%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECostco%20rotisserie%20chickens%20are%20timestamped.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20David%20and%20Susan%20previously%20told%20me%2C%20Costco's%20famous%20%244.99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fcostco-rotisserie-chicken-only-sold-for-few-hours-fans-say-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erotisserie%20chickens%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20timestamped%20the%20moment%20they%20leave%20the%20oven.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20are%20then%20put%20on%20display%20for%20approximately%20two%20hours.%20If%20they%20don't%20sell%2C%20the%20chickens%20are%20removed%20and%20repurposed%20for%20other%20grocery%20items%20such%20as%20soups%2C%20salads%2C%20tacos%2C%20and%20more%2C%20the%20couple%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECostco%20shoppers%20can%20get%20their%20money%20back%20if%20they%20buy%20avocados%20that%20don't%20ripen%20correctly%2C%20Susan%20said.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Costco%20accepts%20returns%20on%20produce%20that%20doesn't%20ripen%20correctly.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656f91830ec98e92f74c63b8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECostco%20accepts%20returns%20on%20produce%20that%20doesn't%20ripen%20correctly%2C%20according%20to%20Susan.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20final%20sections%20I%20toured%20with%20David%20and%20Susan%20was%20the%20fresh%20produce%20area.%20As%20we%20strolled%20around%2C%20Susan%20brought%20my%20attention%20to%20the%20cardboard%20crates%20displaying%20bags%20of%20green%20avocados.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20avocados%20are%20great%2C%26quot%3B%20Susan%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20they%20don't%20ripen%20properly%2C%20you%20bring%20them%20back%20and%20they%20take%20them%20back%20and%20then%20give%20you%20refunds%20with%20no%20discussions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Susan%2C%20having%20an%20entire%20batch%20of%20avocados%20go%20bad%20isn't%20a%20common%20occurrence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20happens%20rarely%2C%20but%20sometimes%20they%20could%20just%20all%20go%20black%20or%20something%20will%20be%20wrong%20with%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20bring%20them%20back%20and%20go%2C%20'These%20didn't%20ripen%20well%2C'%20and%20get%20money%20back.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EEven%20though%20Susan%20and%20David%20are%20Costco%20veterans%2C%20they%20are%20still%20shocked%20by%20how%20random%20Costco's%20product%20placement%20appears.%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Items%20are%20sometimes%20haphazardly%20sold%20next%20to%20each%20other%20in%20no%20particular%20order.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656f923b58e7c0c29a29e8ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EItems%20are%20sometimes%20sold%20next%20to%20each%20other%20in%20no%20particular%20order.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20someone%20with%20very%20hazy%20memories%20of%20shopping%20at%20Costco%20as%20a%20kid%2C%20I%20was%20surprised%20by%20how%20random%20the%20stock%20in%20most%20of%20the%20aisles%20seemed.%20As%20we%20ventured%20through%20different%20sections%2C%20I%20spotted%20items%20like%20Duracell%20batteries%20sold%20next%20to%20a%20singular%20keyboard%20set%2C%20sneakers%20next%20to%20washing%20machines%2C%20and%20waxed%20Amaryllis%20bulbs%20next%20to%20Command%20strips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20so%20random%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20said%20to%20David%20and%20Susan%2C%20expecting%20them%20to%20have%20an%20explanation%20of%20the%20method%20behind%20the%20madness.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20other%20than%20saying%20that%20the%20store%20layout%20is%20more%20carefully%20planned%20out%20than%20it%20might%20appear%2C%20they%20didn't%20offer%20a%20concrete%20answer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20the%20couple%20did%20tell%20me%20that%20Costco's%20randomness%20is%20part%20of%20the%20fun%20of%20shopping%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWelcome%20to%20Costco%2C%26quot%3B%20Susan%20said%2C%20as%20we%20went%20from%20an%20aisle%20selling%20chocolates%20to%20one%20selling%20car%20batteries.%20David%20chuckled%20in%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20biggest%20compliment%20you%20can%20give%20a%20Costco%20employee%20is%20that%20the%20section%20they%20are%20covering%20looks%20%26quot%3Bshowtime%20ready.%26quot%3B%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Costco%20employee%20clearing%20reorganizing%20stacks%20of%20boxes.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656f92d158e7c0c29a29e967%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Costco%20employee%20clearing%20reorganizing%20stacks%20of%20boxes.%3Cp%3EMaria%20Noyen%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EToward%20the%20end%20of%20our%20tour%2C%20Susan%20and%20David%20paused%20to%20approach%20a%20Costco%20employee%20who%20was%20working%20on%20de-boxing%20empty%20cartons%20of%20fruit%20juice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stood%20and%20watched%20as%20they%20engaged%20in%20a%20quick%20conversation%2C%20which%20ended%20with%20the%20employee%20giving%20a%20warm%20thanks%20before%20returning%20to%20his%20task.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20was%20that%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20asked%20the%20couple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20compliment%20you%20can%20give%20is%20showtime%20ready%2C%26quot%3B%20Susan%20said.%20As%20they%20previously%20told%20me%2C%20the%20phrase%20is%20used%20by%20Costco%20employees%20to%20refer%20to%20how%20pristinely%20organized%20a%20warehouse%20is%20when%20it%20opens.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETelling%20an%20employee%20that%20the%20section%20they%20are%20working%20on%20looks%20%26quot%3Bshowtime%20ready%26quot%3B%20is%20just%20another%20way%20of%20saying%20they've%20done%20an%20amazing%20organizational%20job%2C%20which%20is%20something%20Costco%20has%20always%20prided%20itself%20on%2C%20according%20to%20Susan%20and%20David.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-surprising-things-i-learned-shopping-with-superfans-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702208281000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65737ad57a3c8094d5db474e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-surprising-things-i-learned-shopping-with-superfans-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Costco%20newbie%20joined%20superfans%20David%20and%20Susan%20Schwartz%20on%20a%20tour%20of%20the%20Brooklyn%20location%20and%20made%20plenty%20of%20surprising%20discoveries%20along%20the%20way.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mnoyen%40insider.com%20(Maria%20Noyen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-surprising-things-i-learned-shopping-with-superfans-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Legendary%20investor%20Charlie%20Munger%20shared%20his%20regrets%2C%20mistakes%2C%20and%20life%20lessons%20in%20his%20final%20TV%20interview.%20Here%20are%20the%2018%20best%20quotes.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22charlie%20munger%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F600aa21cc94799001992cb50%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221750%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20late%20Charlie%20Munger.%3Cp%3ELane%20Hickenbottom%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ECharlie%20Munger%20discussed%20his%20regrets%20and%20shared%20life%20lessons%20during%20his%20final%20TV%20interview.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWarren%20Buffett's%20late%20business%20partner%20talked%20sports%2C%20fishing%2C%20teenage%20vices%2C%20and%20Alibaba.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMunger%20said%20he%20could%20have%20been%20a%20trillionaire%20instead%20of%20a%20billionaire%20if%20he%20made%20better%20moves.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECharlie%20Munger%20tackled%20topics%20ranging%20from%20his%20teenage%20vices%20to%20the%20secrets%20of%20Berkshire%20Hathaway's%20success%20in%20his%20final%20TV%20interview%2C%20released%20in%20full%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarren%20Buffett's%20late%20business%20partner%20and%20Berkshire's%20vice%20chairman%2C%20who%20died%20aged%2099%20last%20week%2C%20touched%20on%20everything%20from%20Alibaba%20and%20fishing%20to%20sports%20and%20psychology%20in%20his%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbuffett.cnbc.com%2Fvideo%2F2023%2F12%2F05%2Fcharlie-mungers-final-cnbc-interview.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econversation%20with%20CNBC%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20also%20suggested%20that%20he%20could%20have%20been%20a%20trillionaire%20if%20he'd%20worked%20harder%20and%20smarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHere%20are%20Munger's%2018%20best%20quotes%20from%20the%20interview%2C%20lightly%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20%26quot%3BI%20bought%20the%20complete%20writings%20of%20Sigmund%20Freud%20from%20the%20area%20library.%20It%20was%20one%20big%20book.%20And%20I%20went%20through%20it%20very%20laboriously.%20And%20I%20realized%20he%20was%20a%20goddamn%20lunatic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20%26quot%3BI%20tried%20to%20learn%20to%20smoke%20so%20I%20could%20be%20a%20cool%20kid%20like%20the%20other%20kids%20in%20high%20school.%20I%20tried%20to%20ruin%20my%20life%2C%20but%20it%20nauseated%20me.%20And%20so%20I%20said%2C%20'The%20hell%20with%20this.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20enough%20alcoholics%20and%20near-alcoholics%20in%20my%20own%20family%20that%20made%20me%20worry%20about%20liquor.%20I%20was%20always%20very%20cautious%20about%20drinking%20any%20liquor.%20Now%2C%20I%20did%20occasionally%20get%20drunk%20and%20throw%20up.%20That%20gave%20me%20the%20nausea%20which%20enabled%20me%20to%20give%20up%20liquor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4.%20%26quot%3BI%20drink%20Diet%20Coke.%20I'm%20sure%20it%20shortens%20my%20life%20a%20little.%20But%20I%20don't%20give%20a%20damn%20about%20the%20last%20week%20of%20lying%20there%20unconscious%3B%20it's%20only%20the%20good%20part%20of%20life%20I%20want%20anyway.%20Diet%20Coke%20may%20be%20helping%20me%20skip%20it.%20But%20who%20knows%3F%20It's%20helping%20me%20skip%20the%20last%20month%2C%20not%20the%20first%20month.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E5.%20%26quot%3BMy%20game%20in%20life%20was%20always%20to%20avoid%20all%20standard%20ways%20of%20failing.%20You%20teach%20me%20the%20wrong%20way%20to%20play%20poker%20and%20I%20will%20avoid%20it.%20You%20teach%20me%20the%20wrong%20way%20to%20do%20something%20else%2C%20I%20will%20avoid%20it.%20I've%20avoided%20a%20lot%20because%20I'm%20so%20cautious.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E6.%20%26quot%3BWe%20got%20a%20little%20less%20crazy%20than%20most%20people%2C%20and%20a%20little%20less%20stupid%20than%20most%20people%2C%20and%20that%20really%20helped%20us.%20Then%20in%20addition%2C%20we%20were%20given%20this%20much%20longer%20time%20to%20run%20than%20most%20people%2C%20because%20something%20kept%20us%20alive%20into%20our%2090s.%20Those%20are%20the%20two%20things%20that%20really%20happened.%26quot%3B%20(Munger%20was%20asked%20about%20the%20secret%20to%20Berkshire's%20success.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E7.%20%26quot%3BThe%20main%20trick%20that%20Berkshire%20shows%20is%20the%20power%20of%20what%20I%20call%20the%20Wooden%20effect.%20Wooden%20was%20the%20most%20famous%20basketball%20coach%20of%20a%20whole%20era.%20He%20concentrated%20about%2090%25%20of%20the%20playing%20time%20in%20seven%20players.%20That%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20great%20system%20for%20winning%20at%20basketball%3B%20you%20learn%20by%20playing%20in%20a%20way%20you%20can%20never%20learn%20just%20by%20shooting%20practice%20baskets.%26quot%3B%20(Munger%20was%20referring%20to%20Berkshire%20concentrating%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20its%20funds%20in%20its%20very%20best%20bets%20like%20Coca-Cola%20and%20American%20Express.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E8.%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20something%20big%20to%20come%20along%2C%20and%20use%20up%20all%20our%20cash%2C%20and%20some%20borrowing.%20But%20who's%20more%20likely%20to%20find%20something%20than%20a%20guy%20who%20has%20%24160%20billion%20in%20cash%2C%20plus%20a%20long%20history%20of%20buying%20bargains%3F%26quot%3B%20(Munger%20was%20referring%20to%20Berkshire's%20current%20cash%20pile%20and%20its%20struggle%20to%20find%20compelling%20acquisitions%20in%20recent%20years.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E9.%20%26quot%3BMy%20worst%20trade%20was%20buying%20a%20block%20for%20the%20Munger%20family%20in%20Alibaba%2C%20which%20is%20a%20pretty%20good%20company.%20But%20I%20think%20it%20got%20overhyped%2C%20and%20Jack%20Ma%20made%20mistakes%20in%20dealing%20with%20the%20Chinese%20government.%20Everybody%20has%20some%20bad%20ones.%20The%20greatest%20tennis%20player%20goes%20out%20there%20some%20days%20to%20the%20center%20court%20and%20has%20a%20bad%20day.%20It%20happens.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E10.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20all%20that%20pleased.%20I%20basically%20screwed%20up.%20I%20could%20have%20done%20a%20lot%20better%20if%20I%20had%20been%20a%20little%20smarter%2C%20a%20little%20quicker.%20I%20might%20have%20had%20multiple%20trillions%20instead%20of%20multiple%20billions.%20I%20do%20think%20about%20what%20I%20missed%20by%20being%20just%20not%20quite%20smart%20enough%20or%20hardworking%20enough.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E11.%20%26quot%3BWe%20both%20watched%20our%20friends%20who%20got%20rich%20build%20these%20really%20fancy%20houses.%20In%20practically%20every%20case%2C%20they%20made%20the%20person%20less%20happy%2C%20not%20happier.%20Having%20a%20really%20fancy%20house%2C%20it's%20good%20for%20entertaining%20100%20people%20at%20once.%20It's%20a%20very%20expensive%20thing%20to%20do.%20And%20it%20doesn't%20do%20you%20that%20much%20good.%20I%20decided%20not%20to%20live%20a%20life%20where%20I%20look%20like%20the%20Duke%20of%20Westchester%20or%20something.%20I%20didn't%20think%20it%20would%20be%20good%20for%20the%20children.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E12.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20very%20good%20at%20learning%20things%20from%20dead%20people.%26quot%3B%20(Munger%20was%20a%20voracious%20reader%20who%20counted%20Benjamin%20Franklin%20among%20his%20role%20models.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E13.%20%26quot%3BDo%20not%20live%20your%20life%20in%20such%20a%20fashion%20that%20a%20bad%20day%20can%20kill%20you.%26quot%3B%20(Munger%20meant%20that%20investors%20should%20never%20bet%20so%20heavily%20and%20take%20on%20so%20much%20leverage%20that%20they%20can%20lose%20it%20all%20if%20a%20trade%20goes%20wrong.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E14.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20a%20hitter%20at%20baseball%20who%20tries%20to%20hit%20a%20home%20run%20on%20every%20pitch.%20The%20great%20home%20runners%20do%20not%20remotely%20swing%20at%20every%20pitch.%20They%20wait%20for%20one%20that%20they%20can%20really%20handle.%20And%20that's%20what%20great%20stock%20traders%20do%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E15.%20%26quot%3BYou%20only%20get%20a%20few%20trips%20to%20the%20pie%20counter.%20If%20you%20take%20out%20of%20Warren%20Buffett's%20life%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarren-buffett-annual-shareholder-letter-coke-amex-buybacks-taxes-earnings-2023-2%5C%22%3E10%20most%20important%20trips%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20pie%20counter%2C%20his%20whole%20record%20would%20look%20like%20dung.%20We%20knew%20enough%20to%20take%20a%20good%20helping%20when%20we%20were%20offered%20a%20trip%20to%20the%20pie%20counter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E16.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20we%20did%20take%20way%20smaller%20a%20helping%20than%20we%20could've%20easily%20handled.%20Berkshire%20could%20easily%20be%20worth%20twice%20what%20it%20is%20now.%20And%20the%20extra%20risk%20we%20would've%20taken%20would've%20been%20practically%20nothing.%20All%20we%20had%20to%20do%20is%20just%20a%20little%20more%20leverage%20that%20was%20easily%20available.%20The%20reason%20we%20didn't%20is%20the%20idea%20of%20disappointing%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20had%20trusted%20us.%26quot%3B%20(Munger%20was%20referring%20to%20Berkshire's%20shareholders.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E17.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20so%20old%20and%20weak%20compared%20to%20what%20I%20was%20when%20I%20was%2096%2C%20that%20I%20no%20longer%20want%20to%20catch%20a%20200-pound%20tuna.%20It's%20just%20too%20goddamn%20much%20work%20to%20get%20it%20in.%20It%20takes%20too%20much%20physical%20strength.%20So%20I%20would%20have%20paid%20any%20amount%20to%20catch%20a%20200-pound%20tuna%20when%20I%20was%20younger%3B%20I%20never%20caught%20one.%20And%20now%20if%20given%20the%20opportunity%2C%20I%20would%20just%20decline%20going.%20I%20won't%20even%20go%20out%20after%20them.%20There%20are%20things%20you%20give%20up%20with%20time.%26quot%3B%20(Munger%20was%20asked%20if%20there%20was%20anything%20he%20didn't%20tick%20off%20his%20bucket%20list.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E18.%20%26quot%3BI%20basically%20believe%20in%20the%20soldier%20on%20system.%20Lots%20of%20hardship%20will%20come%20and%20you've%20got%20to%20handle%20it%20well%20by%20soldiering%20through.%20A%20few%20rare%20opportunities%20will%20come.%20You've%20got%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20recognize%20them%20when%20they%20come%2C%20and%20not%20make%20too%20minor%20of%20a%20trip%20to%20the%20pie%20counter%20when%20the%20opportunity%20is%20available.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%