n's%20%26quot%3Blogistics%20hell.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla's%20salvation%20came%20in%20the%20form%20of%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party.%20In%202019%2C%20as%20executives%20were%20fleeing%20Tesla%20and%20the%20company%20continued%20to%20bleed%20cash%2C%20Musk%20struck%20a%20deal%20to%20build%20a%20factory%20in%20Shanghai.%20From%20permitting%20to%20construction%20to%20opening%2C%20the%20Shanghai%20Gigafactory%20was%20built%20in%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2019-10-23%2Felon-musk-opened-tesla-s-shanghai-gigafactory-in-just-168-days%3Fembedded-checkout%3Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E168%20working%20days%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Skeptical%20observers%20%E2%80%94%20myself%20included%20%E2%80%94%20were%20blindsided.%20What%20we%20failed%20to%20appreciate%20was%20the%20staggering%20power%20of%20the%20CCP%20when%20it's%20aggressively%20pushing%20to%20meet%20a%20single%20goal.%20When%20the%20party%20said%20Tesla%20could%20build%20the%20factory%20there%2C%20that%20meant%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20China%2C%20Tesla%20would%20not%20have%20finally%20turned%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Breal%20car%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20Musk's%20own%20words.%20He%20dodged%20destruction%20and%20started%20to%20settle%20down%20and%20focus%20on%20other%20projects%2C%20like%20Starlink.%20Sure%2C%20he%20was%20still%20wilding%20out%20on%20Twitter%2C%20but%20at%20least%20he%20wasn't%20bawling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rollingstone.com%2Fculture%2Fculture-features%2Felon-musk-the-architect-of-tomorrow-120850%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20Rolling%20Stone%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20how%20badly%20he%20needs%20a%20girlfriend%20to%20be%20happy.%20At%20last%2C%20it%20seemed%20the%20Musk%20universe%20had%20found%20some%20kind%20of%20frenzied%20equilibrium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20there%20are%20two%20different%20lessons%20a%20person%20can%20take%20from%20surviving%20a%20brush%20with%20near%20ruin.%20They%20can%20learn%20to%20be%20more%20cautious%2C%20or%20they%20can%20decide%20that%20they%20are%20indestructible%20and%20tempt%20fate.%20I%20don't%20think%20I%20need%20to%20tell%20you%20which%20path%20Musk%20chose.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAll%20of%20Elon%20world%20is%20connected%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESay%20what%20you%20want%20about%20him%2C%20but%20Elon%20Musk%20has%20ambition.%20On%20top%20of%20the%20world%20in%20early%202022%2C%20Musk%20decided%20that%20he%20had%20the%20power%20to%20single-handedly%20%26quot%3Bfix%26quot%3B%20the%20entire%20concept%20of%20free%20speech.%20And%20given%20that%20he%20is%20hopelessly%20addicted%20to%20the%20adulation%20he%20gets%20from%20Twitter%2C%20that's%20where%20he%20figured%20he%20would%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20all%20know%20this%20part%20of%20the%20story.%20Musk%20started%20building%20a%20stake%20in%20Twitter%20in%20early%202022%2C%20then%20offered%20to%20buy%20it%20outright.%20He%20offered%20such%20a%20ridiculously%20high%20price%20that%20the%20board%20couldn't%20say%20no.%20A%20consortium%20of%20banks%20%E2%80%94%20led%20by%20Morgan%20Stanley%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-margin-loan-twitter-takeover-morgan-stanley-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloaned%20him%20a%20large%20portion%20of%20the%20money%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20finally%2C%20after%20trying%20and%20then%20failing%20to%20renege%20on%20the%20deal%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-reach-agreement-to-close-acquisition-deal-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehe%20bought%20Twitter%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Not%20long%20after%20completing%20the%20deal%2C%20Musk%20exhausted%20all%20the%20ideas%20to%20turn%20around%20the%20platform%20and%20was%20left%20with%20angry%20former%20employees%2C%20skeptical%20advertisers%2C%20a%20terrible%20new%20name%2C%20and%20a%20massive%20pile%20of%20debt%20owed%20to%20the%20Boy%20Scouts%20over%20on%20Wall%20Street.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENowadays%2C%20some%20analysts%2C%20like%20Vicki%20Bryan%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20research%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbondangle.substack.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBond%20Angle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20suspect%20that%20Twitter%20is%20spending%20much%20more%20than%20it's%20able%20to%20generate%20or%20borrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20company%20still%20burning%20cash%20and%20%241.3-1.5%20billion%20in%20annual%20interest%20due%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20I%20had%20expected%20Twitter%20to%20live%20on%20borrowed%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Bryan%20wrote%20in%20a%20note%20to%20clients.%20She%20said%20that%20even%20if%20Twitter%20tapped%20the%20loans%20available%20to%20it%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20year%2C%20the%20company%20may%20be%20almost%20out%20of%20options.%20%26quot%3BThe%20year%20is%20over%2C%20so%20Twitter's%20cash%20may%20be%20nearly%20if%20not%20already%20dried%20up%E2%80%94along%20with%20Elon%20Musk's%20options%2C%26quot%3B%20Bryan%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20the%20way%20that%20Musk%20operates%2C%20the%20social-media%20company's%20troubles%20pose%20a%20threat%20to%20his%20whole%20business%20empire.%20Despite%20being%20the%20second-wealthiest%20person%20in%20the%20world%2C%20Musk%20is%20curiously%20cash%20poor.%20He%20doesn't%20take%20a%20salary%20from%20Tesla%2C%20and%20while%20he%20owns%20about%2020%25%20of%20the%20EV%20maker%2C%20public%20documents%20filed%20in%20March%20show%20that%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2Fix%3Fdoc%3D%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F1318605%2F000119312523094075%2Fd451342ddef14a.htm%23toc451342_59%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E63%25%20of%20those%20shares%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20%26quot%3Bpledged%20as%20collateral%20to%20secure%20certain%20personal%20indebtedness.%26quot%3B%20You%20know%2C%20like%20the%20private%20jets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20why%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-takeover-money-sucking-quagmire-tesla-spacex-debt-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eusing%20Tesla%20stock%20to%20source%20cash%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20the%20time%20gets%20hairy.%20If%20Tesla%20shares%20fall%20below%20a%20certain%20level%2C%20the%20banks%20can%20call%20in%20those%20personal%20loans%20%E2%80%94%20leaving%20Musk%20on%20the%20hook.%20And%20the%20quickest%20way%20for%20Tesla's%20stock%20to%20drop%20off%20a%20cliff%20is%20for%20investors%20to%20get%20wind%20of%20a%20big%20Musk%20sale.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20he%20needs%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20he%20still%20holds%20on%20to%20all%20the%20Tesla%20stock%20he's%20pledged%20as%20collateral%20to%20the%20banks.%20Unfortunately%2C%20though%2C%20the%20easiest%20way%20for%20Musk%20to%20fill%20the%20gaping%20hole%20in%20Twitter's%20balance%20sheet%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20sell%20Tesla%20shares.%20You%20see%20how%20this%20could%20be%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20when%20he's%20really%20hard%20up%2C%20Musk%20borrows%20money%20from%20SpaceX%20%E2%80%94%20a%20private%20company%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Ftech%2Fbehind-the-curtain-of-elon-musks-secretive-spacex-revenue-growth-and-rising-costs-2c828e2b%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elost%20a%20combined%20%241.5%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%20and%202022.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Felon-musk-spacex-loan-269a2168%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eborrowed%20%241%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20company%20when%20he%20bought%20Twitter%20and%20paid%20the%20loan%20back%20within%20a%20month%20%E2%80%94%20but%20he%20had%20to%20sell%20%244%20billion%20worth%20of%20Tesla%20shares%20to%20do%20it.%20Using%20his%20wealth%20and%20power%2C%20Musk%20has%20built%20himself%20a%20separate%20reality%20where%20there%20are%20no%20real%20consequences%20for%20the%20risks%20he%20takes%2C%20but%20keeping%20the%20lights%20on%20at%20Twitter%20%E2%80%94%20sorry%2C%20X%20%E2%80%94%20is%20testing%20its%20limits%20more%20and%20more%20by%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELife%20on%20Earth%201%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20money-incinerating%20activity%2C%20from%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20Twitter%20deal%20to%20this%20very%20moment%2C%20could%20not%20have%20come%20at%20a%20worse%20time.%20For%20decades%2C%20Musk%20has%20operated%20in%20a%20placid%20economy%20where%20interest%20rates%20were%20near%20zero.%20But%20Musk%20started%20buying%20Twitter%20right%20as%20central%20banks%20around%20the%20world%20began%20hiking%20rates%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20combat%20inflation.%20That%20means%20the%20cost%20of%20servicing%20his%20debt%20is%20getting%20more%20expensive%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20him%20to%20get%20new%20loans.%20It's%20a%20shift%20so%20dramatic%20that%20it%20could%20rip%20a%20hole%20in%20the%20universe%20through%20which%20Musk's%20reality%20collapses%20into%20our%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20outlook%20for%20Tesla's%20business%20doesn't%20help%20him%20much%20either.%20The%20company's%20share%20of%20the%20EV%20market%20has%20fallen%20as%20competitors%20have%20swarmed%20in.%20The%20new%20entrants%20prompted%20Musk%20to%20start%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-model-3-model-y-less-than-average-gas-car-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecutting%20prices%20for%20his%20cars%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%202023%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-tesla-price-cuts-electric-cars-losing-business-strategy-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETesla's%20profitability%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20under%20serious%20pressure.%20The%20company%20has%20plans%20to%20expand%20its%20manufacturing%20capability%2C%20but%20no%20plans%20to%20refresh%20its%20aging%20fleet%20of%20vehicles.%20Unless%2C%20of%20course%2C%20you%20count%20the%20Cybertuck%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjalopnik.com%2Ftesla-offers-1-000-to-cybertruck-reservation-holders-t-1851065528%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhich%20most%20do%20not%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Last%20month%2C%20Tesla%20threw%20a%20launch%20event%20to%20celebrate%20the%20delivery%20of%2010%20Cybertrucks.%20Ten.%20The%20least%20expensive%20model%2C%20priced%20at%20%2460%2C000%2C%20will%20not%20be%20available%20until%202025%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company.%20Bryan%20told%20me%20that%20she%20expects%20Musk%20to%20continue%20to%20siphon%20money%20from%20Tesla%20in%20obscure%20ways%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20question%20is%3A%20How%20much%20money%20will%20there%20be%20to%20siphon%2C%20exactly%3F%20And%20for%20how%20long%20will%20he%20need%20to%20do%20that%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20only%20thing%20we're%20waiting%20on%20is%20for%20Elon%20to%20cry%20uncle%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bryan.%20In%20her%20view%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20based%20on%2030%20years%20of%20investing%20in%20distressed%20assets%20%E2%80%94%20any%20equity%20in%20the%20company%20has%20already%20been%20erased%20by%20Musk's%20antics.%20As%20for%20the%20debt%2C%20the%20banks%20have%20been%20unable%20to%20unload%20it%20at%2085%20cents%20on%20the%20dollar%2C%20and%20she%20thinks%20they'll%20be%20lucky%20to%20get%2040%20cents.%20By%20all%20accounts%2C%20Twitter%20has%20a%20credit%20problem%2C%20and%20Bryan%20said%20that%20calls%20for%20a%20run-of-the-mill%20restructuring%20solution%3A%20bankruptcy.%20When%20Musk%20tires%20of%20robbing%20Peter%20to%20pay%20Paul%2C%20he%20will%20default%20on%20his%20Twitter%20loans.%20Then%20the%20consortium%20of%20banks%20that%20own%20the%20debt%20can%20accelerate%20it%20%E2%80%94%20standard%20debt%20agreements%20come%20with%20clauses%20that%20allow%20lenders%20to%20force%20a%20borrower%20to%20pay%20all%20of%20an%20outstanding%20loan%20back%20if%20certain%20requirements%20(like%20payment)%20are%20not%20met.%20Once%20that%20wire%20is%20tripped%2C%20Twitter%20can%20declare%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20money%20that%20has%20been%20set%20on%20fire%20that%20is%20never%20coming%20back%2C%26quot%3B%20Bryan%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20in%20the%20salvage%20business%20with%20Twitter.%20In%20a%20restructuring%2C%20with%20Elon%20gone%2C%20you%20can%20have%20people%20looking%20at%20it.%20They%20can%20foresee%20that%20Elon%20didn't%20do%20anything%20that%20can't%20be%20reversed%20and%20offer%20instant%20relief.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWill%20it%20be%20enough%20to%20save%20Twitter%2FX%3F%20Maybe%20not%2C%20but%20it's%20the%20company's%20only%20and%20best%20hope.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWall%20Street%20should%20be%20thoroughly%20embarrassed.%20According%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Ftech%2Fone-year-on-twitter-continues-to-burn-a-hole-through-bank-balance-sheets-d92dfe12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20banks%20holding%20Twitter's%20debt%20are%20already%20expecting%20to%20take%20a%20%242%20billion%20hit%20when%20they%20can%20finally%20sell%20it%20off.%20It's%20not%20hard%20to%20see%20why.%20I've%20said%20from%20the%20jump%20that%20there%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter-takeover-money-sucking-quagmire-tesla-spacex-debt-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20money%20in%20this%20Twitter%20venture%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20no%20principles%20either.%20Musk%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-killed-twitter-irrelevant-meta-threads-debt-mark-zuckerberg-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealways%20going%20to%20turn%20Twitter%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20a%20reflection%20of%20his%20limited%20view%2C%20his%20%26quot%3BEarth%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20as%20he%20put%20it%20during%20his%20manic%20rambling%20at%20Dealbook%20%E2%80%94%20not%20a%20place%20for%20the%20average%20user.%20I%20never%20expected%20Musk's%20fanboys%20to%20understand%20that%2C%20but%20I%20did%20expect%20bankers%20who%20are%20supposed%20to%20understand%20who%20pays%20for%20what%20in%20a%20media%20business%20to%20get%20it.%20In%20the%20end%2C%20there's%20a%20real%20chance