eople%20stay%20indoors.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20that%20way%3A%20So-called%20%26quot%3Bwinter%20cities%26quot%3B%20are%20built%20to%20be%20used%20year-round.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDesigning%20cities%20to%20be%20fun%20and%20accessible%20in%20the%20winter%20is%20good%20for%20business%20and%20people.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Jennifer%20Seabolt%20moved%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboston-portland-chicago-new-job-where-move-rto-higher-pay-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHawaii%20to%20Boston%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20seven%20years%20ago%2C%20she%20prepared%20herself%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworst-winters-in-america-photos-snow-temperature-records-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewinter%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20wasn't%20the%20cold%20that%20got%20her%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdaylight-saving-time-is-deadly-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehow%20dark%20and%20gloomy%20things%20would%20get%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrying%20to%20rally%20friends%20or%20family%20to%20leave%20home%20when%20it's%20cold%20and%20dark%20outside%20is%20hard%2C%20in%20part%20because%20it%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20there's%20a%20lot%20to%20do%2C%20she%20said.%20And%20most%20activities%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-cost-of-living-alcohol-coffee-going-out-more-expensive-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Einvolve%20spending%20money%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20unlike%20the%20free%20outdoor%20events%20that%20seem%20easier%20to%20access%20during%20warmer%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20absolutely%20more%20of%20an%20effort%2C%20I%20think%2C%20to%20try%20to%20do%20things%20during%20the%20winter%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeabolt%20isn't%20alone.%20In%20many%20American%20cities%2C%20outdoor%20spaces%20shutter%20for%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20year.%20In%20a%20time%20when%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-epidemic-solutions-investment-venture-capital-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloneliness%20epidemic%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20raging%20%E2%80%94%20and%20cities%20are%20still%20struggling%20to%20rebound%20economically%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epandemic%20%E2%80%94%20city%20life%20shutting%20down%20for%20a%20whole%20season%20may%20exacerbate%20existing%20social%20and%20economic%20problems.%20That's%20where%20the%20concept%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bwinter%20city%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20designed%20to%20not%20only%20be%20livable%2C%20but%20actually%20enjoyable%2C%20during%20the%20chilly%20season%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecomes%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWinter%20cities%20are%20defined%20by%20a%20few%20basic%20design%20principles%2C%20according%20to%20Isla%20Tanaka%2C%20the%20winter%20city%20planner%20for%20the%20Canadian%20city%20of%20Edmonton%2C%20Alberta%3A%20Putting%20public%20spaces%20in%20areas%20that%20receive%20sunshine%2C%20blocking%20wind%2C%20incorporating%20pops%20of%20color%20into%20an%20otherwise%20dreary%20landscape%2C%20lighting%20up%20spaces%20so%20they're%20still%20usable%20during%20long%20winter%20nights%2C%20and%20crafting%20infrastructure%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0like%20fire%20pits%20or%20public%20bathrooms%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0to%20support%20life%20in%20the%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20fire%20pit%20in%20Edmonton%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657233d558e7c0c29a2acde0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20fire%20pit%20in%20Edmonton.%3Cp%3EWhy%20Edmonton%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Edmonton%2C%20which%20has%20been%20making%20itself%20a%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewinter%20city%20for%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20initiatives%20include%20developing%20a%20four-season%20patio%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20the%20city%20now%20has%20over%2020%20venues%20with%20winter%20patios%2C%20up%20from%20around%20what%20Tanaka%20estimates%20was%20four%20to%20five%20patios%20during%20winter%202019-2020.%20The%20patios%20are%20heated%2C%20covered%2C%20or%20otherwise%20cozy%20outdoor%20spaces.%20There%20are%20festivals%20every%20weekend%20from%20November%20through%20mid-March.%20Parks%20now%20have%20bathrooms%20that%20can%20remain%20open%20in%20the%20winter%2C%20as%20well%20as%20year-round%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecafes.%20All%20of%20those%20initiatives%20sprung%20in%20part%20from%20a%20question%20of%20emotion%2C%20rather%20than%20infrastructure%2C%20according%20to%20Tanaka%3A%20%26quot%3BWe%20said%2C%20what%20would%20make%20you%20fall%20in%20love%20with%20your%20city%20in%20winter%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20success%20in%20Edmonton%20has%20been%20a%20change%20in%20culture%2C%20Tanaka%20said.%20It%20turns%20out%20that%20alleyways%20lit%20up%20with%20lightboxes%2C%20artistic%20installations%2C%20and%20warm%20patios%20for%20sipping%20beverages%20is%20enough%20to%20entice%20people%20to%20change%20their%20habits%20and%20embrace%20going%20out%20in%20the%20wintertime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20thought%20that%20shifting%20the%20culture%20would%20be%20one%20of%20the%20hardest%20pieces%20of%20the%20work.%20And%20it%20actually%20happened%20much%20faster%20than%20we%20expected%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20played%20a%20role%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0interest%20in%20outdoor%20activities%20in%20cities%20across%20the%20world%20spiked%20when%20indoor%20spaces%20shut%20down.%20Many%20cities%20are%20leaning%20into%20that%20enthusiasm%20with%20new%20programming%20and%20infrastructure%20to%20get%20people%20out%20of%20their%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Members%20of%20the%20public%20and%20invited%20guests%20skate%20on%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20season%20at%20Wollman%20Rink%20in%20Central%20Park%20on%20October%2023%2C%202022%20in%20New%20York%20City.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6571f6ba7a3c8094d5daa549%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22853%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMembers%20of%20the%20public%20and%20invited%20guests%20skate%20on%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20season%20at%20Wollman%20Rink%20in%20Central%20Park%20on%20October%2023%2C%202022%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3Cp%3EAlexi%20Rosenfeld%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EIf%20you%20build%20it%2C%20they%20will%20come%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20recent%20Sunday%20night%20in%20Brooklyn%2C%20New%20York%2C%20light%20rain%20and%20low%20temperatures%20didn't%20stop%20nearly%202%2C000%20people%20from%20weaving%20their%20way%20through%20the%20Brooklyn%20Botanic%20Garden's%20mile-long%20holiday%20light%20show.%20The%20immersive%20%26quot%3BLightscape%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20stroller-%20and%20wheelchair-friendly%2C%20is%20bringing%20people%20outside%20at%20a%20time%20of%20year%20when%20the%20Garden%20would%20normally%20be%20%26quot%3Bcold%2C%20dark%2C%20and%20closed%20by%204%3A30%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Adrian%20Benepe%2C%20the%20Botanic%20Garden's%20president%20and%20CEO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBenepe%2C%20a%20former%20NYC%20Parks%20Commissioner%2C%20says%20interest%20in%20outdoor%20activities%20in%20the%20city%20has%20surged%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20accelerated%20by%20the%20pandemic.%20When%20the%20Botanic%20Garden%20debuted%20its%20Lightscape%20show%20in%20November%202020%2C%20he%20was%20blown%20away%20by%20attendance.%20The%20show%20attracted%20more%20than%20150%2C000%20visitors%20during%20its%20six%20weeks%2C%20Benepe%20said%2C%20during%20a%20time%20of%20year%20when%20the%20Garden%20normally%20gets%20between%205%2C000%20and%2010%2C000%20visitors%20a%20month.%20It's%20a%20financial%20boon%20during%20the%20Garden's%20slowest%20time%20of%20year%2C%20and%20good%20for%20the%20institution's%20brand.%20It's%20also%20good%20for%20public%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20addition%20to%20just%20being%20a%20source%20of%20enlivening%20cultural%20institutions%20that%20would%20otherwise%20be%20closed%20and%20dark%2C%20it's%20building%20community%2C%20it%20creates%20antidotes%20to%20winter%20lethargy%20and%20to%20loneliness%2C%26quot%3B%20Benepe%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%2C%20real%20public%20health%20reasons%20to%20do%20these%20things%2C%20to%20encourage%20people%20to%20get%20outdoors%20in%20the%20winter.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22One%20of%20the%20installations%20at%20the%20Brooklyn%20Botanic%20Garden's%20%26quot%3BLightscape%26quot%3B%20show%20on%20December%203%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6571f43f0ec98e92f74d249b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOne%20of%20the%20installations%20at%20the%20Brooklyn%20Botanic%20Garden's%20%26quot%3BLightscape%26quot%3B%20show%20on%20December%203%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EEliza%20Relman%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWinter%20light%20shows%20are%20catching%20on.%20The%20Botanic%20Garden%20installation%20is%20one%20of%20about%2020%20outdoor%20light%20attractions%20in%20the%20New%20York%20City%20metro%20area%20this%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20the%20first%20time%20Benepe%20has%20overseen%20a%20hugely%20successful%20effort%20to%20get%20people%20into%20parks%20during%20the%20coldest%20time%20of%20year.%20While%20he%20was%20parks%20commissioner%2C%20he%20helped%20realize%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2020%2F06%2F01%2Farts%2Fdesign%2Fchristo-appraisal-gates.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EChristo%20and%20Jean-Claude's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Gates%26quot%3B%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%C2%A07%2C500