0many%20downtowns%20are%20hurting%20without%20workers%20patronizing%20their%20businesses%2C%20riding%20mass%20transit%2C%20and%20occupying%20offices.%20The%20phenomenon%20is%20fueling%20warnings%20about%20the%20so-called%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2022%2F11%2F30%2Fopinion%2Fcovid-pandemic-cities-future.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eurban%20doom%20loop%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20As%20office%20vacancies%20rise%2C%20lower%20commercial%20property%20tax%20revenue%20could%20force%20leaders%20to%20curtail%20city%20services%2C%20hurting%20quality%20of%20life%20and%20pushing%20residents%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatrick%20Coleman%2C%20a%20Michigan-based%20urban%20and%20town%20planner%20professional%20who%20runs%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwintercities.com%2Fhome%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EWinter%20Cities%20Institute%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20that%20winter%20cities%20are%20almost%20an%20issue%20of%20%26quot%3Bsurvival%26quot%3B%20for%20chillier%20urban%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20many%20years%2C%20the%20north%20has%20been%20losing%20population%20because%20people%20have%20been%20told%20that%20cold%20is%20bad%2C%20warm%20is%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20Coleman%20said.%20In%20his%20region%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20seniors%20leave%20when%20they%20retire%2C%20moving%20to%20places%20like%20Florida%20or%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20real%20problem.%20I%20mean%2C%20even%20if%20they%20come%20back%20in%20the%20summertime%2C%20still%2C%20their%20dollars%20are%20being%20spent%20somewhere%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Winter%20in%20Edmonton%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6572351b0ec98e92f74d4d67%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEdmonton%20has%20embraced%20all%20kinds%20of%20outdoor%20winter%20activities%2C%20including%20urban%20snowboar