0as%20ours%20are%20my%20spouse's%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eage%20or%20younger.%20They%20all%20graduated%20the%20same%20year%20as%20my%20younger%20sister%20or%20cousins%2C%20years%20behind%20me.%20But%20aside%20from%20me%20knowing%20I'm%20older%20and%20often%20have%20more%20life%20experience%20%E2%80%94%20and%20therefore%20advice%20%E2%80%94%20it%20doesn't%20much%20matter.%20I%20often%20think%20I'm%20the%20only%20one%20who%20even%20takes%20note%20of%20my%20age%20vs.%20theirs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20effect%20our%20age%20difference%20has%20on%20our%20lives%20is%20my%20ability%20to%20carry%20a%20child.%20At%2031%2C%20my%20husband%20remains%20in%20his%20fertile%20prime%2C%20while%20at%20nearly%2037%2C%20if%20I%20were%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Folder-mother-defends-having-children-at-45-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eget%20pregnant%3C%2Fa%3E%20again%2C%20it%20would%20be%20considered%20geriatric.%20It's%20one%20of%20the%20foremost%20factors%20as%20to%20why%20we've%20chosen%20to%20stop%20after%20two%20kids.%20Sure%2C%20we%20could%20plan%20for%20extra%20appointments%2C%20more%20scans%2C%20and%20blood%20draws%20while%20listening%20to%20my%20biological%20clock%20tick%20away.%20But%20instead%2C%20we%20just%20decided%20to%20call%20it%20quits.%20The%20risk%20that%20comes%20with%20my%20age%20simply%20isn't%20worth%20it%20to%20us.%20Plus%2C%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20an%20%26quot%3Bold%20mom%26quot%3B%20who%20doesn't%20have%20the%20energy%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20her%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20married%20someone%20younger%2C%20I%20didn't%20expect%20it%20to%20be%20brought%20up%20so%20often%2C%20especially%20given%20he's%20only%20six%20years%20younger%20than%20I%20am.%20There%20were%20also%20some%20things%20I%20wasn't%20expecting%2C%20like%20cultural%20references%20from%20childhood%20and%20having%20to%20take%20it%20into%20consideration%20when%20planning%20our%20family%3B%20my%20mind%20just%20wasn't%20thinking%20that%20far%