s.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Maxine%20Laceby%2C%20founder%20of%20Absolute%20Collagen.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20single-parent%20household%2C%20with%20an%20alcoholic%20mother.%20We%20had%20nothing.%20I%20left%20school%20at%2016%20and%20after%20working%20in%20a%20factory%20and%20a%20clothes%20shop%2C%20and%20eventually%20ended%20up%20doing%20sales%20and%20marketing%20for%20a%20small%20hotel%20just%20outside%20Bath%20in%20England.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20met%20my%20now%20ex-husband%20at%20the%20hotel%20and%20was%20married%20by%2025.%20He%20was%20successful%20and%20there%20was%20no%20need%20for%20me%20to%20work.%20I%20was%20a%20happy%20stay-at-home%20mom%20for%2020%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20always%20had%20business%20ideas%20but%20couldn't%20get%20them%20moving%20because%20I%20had%20children%20to%20look%20after.%20As%20a%20mother%2C%20I'd%20wake%20up%20every%20day%20and%20think%20%26quot%3BWho%20does%20everyone%20need%20me%20to%20be%20today%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20finally%20found%20time%20for%20myself%20in%20my%20mid-forties%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20split%20when%20I%20was%20in%20my%20mid-forties.%20By%20then%2C%20I'd%20stopped%20doing%20the%20school%20run.%20It%20was%20finally%20time%20to%20put%20myself%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20your%20kids%20leave%20home%20it%20can%20be%20frightening%20having%20all%20that%20free%20time%2C%20but%20I%20found%20it%20liberating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20to%20college%20to%20study%20fine%20arts.%20For%20one%20project%20I%20didn't%20wear%20makeup%20for%20four%20months.%20It%20made%20me%20feel%20ugly%20and%20invisible.%20I%20thought%2C%20if%20I%20was%20going%20to%20strip%20myself%20bare%20for%20this%20project%2C%20I%20needed%20to%20feel%20good%20on%20the%20inside.%20I%20started%20making%20bone%20broth%20from%20scratch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20gave%20me%20a%20sense%20of%20well%20being.%20My%20eyes%20were%20sparkly%2C%20I%20had%20a%20spring%20in%20my%20step%2C%20and%20my%20skin%20became%20so%20dewy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20noticed%20jelly%20forming%20on%20top%20of%20the%20broth%20and%20realized%20this%20hero%20ingredient%20was%20collagen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22905%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Maxine%20Laceby%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655f37649c7d23cb3b9f2d57%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22652%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMaxine%20Laceby%20at%20work%20in%20her%20kitchen%20in%20the%20early%20days%20of%20Absolute%20Collagen.%3Cp%3EMaxine%20Laceby%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EBone%20broth%20was%20a%20gateway%20to%20starting%20a%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202015%20I%20made%20big%20vats%20of%20bone%20broth%20and%20gave%20it%20to%20all%20my%20friends.%20It%20dawned%20on%20me%20that%20if%20they%20were%20enjoying%20it%2C%20why%20can't%20everyone%3F%20I%20was%20a%20single%20parent%20who%20was%20not%20making%20money%2C%20so%20I%20decided%20I%20would%20start%20a%20collagen%20supplement%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDarcy%2C%20my%20eldest%20daughter%2C%20was%20studying%20food%20science%20and%20had%20access%20to%20a%20lab.%20We%20started%20working%20on%20a%20formula%20for%20a%20collagen%20supplement%20in%20our%20kitchen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20found%20that%20marine%20collagen%20was%20far%20superior%20to%20the%20collagen%20in%20broth%20and%20in%202017%20launched%20Absolute%20Collagen.%20The%20business%20was%20self-funded.%20I'd%20sold%20jewelry%2C%20borrowed%20money%2C%20and%20remortgaged%20my%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20everyone's%20eyes%2C%20we%20were%20an%20old%20woman%20and%20recent%20graduate%20with%20no%20business%20experience.%20But%20we%20believed%20in%20our%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20my%20girls%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20it%20goes%20tits%20up%2C%20we%20will%20have%20to%20sell%20the%20house%20and%20buy%20a%20smaller%20one.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIt%20was%20never%20about%20becoming%20a%20very%20successful%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20just%20got%20on%20with%20the%20job%20in%20hand.%20We%20had%20this%20product%20and%20we%20knew%20it%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20house%20was%20full%20of%20collagen%20and%20the%20first%20batch%20had%20to%20be%20thrown%20out%20because%20it%20expired%20before%20we%20could%20sell%20it.%20I%20kept%20overpaying%20people%20because%20I'm%20no%20good%20at%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowth%20happened%20because%20I%20took%20considered%20risks.%20I%20knew%20that%20our%20customers%2C%20or%20%26quot%3BAbsoluters%26quot%3B%20as%20we%20call%20them%2C%20should%20be%20at%20the%20forefront.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20even%20though%20everyone%20was%20saying%20we%20had%20to%20be%20in%20retail%2C%20we%20kept%20it%20all%20direct-to-consumer%20and%20were%20early%20to%20offer%20a%20subscription%20model.%20I%20was%20also%20adamant%20that%20the%20price%20had%20to%20be%20reasonable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20new%20market%20and%20a%20new%20way%20of%20doing%20things%2C%20but%20offering%20a%20great%20product%20and%20getting%20it%20straight%20to%20our%20customers%20worked.%20We%20didn't%20do%20any%20publicity%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0only%20pushing%20our%20customer%20success%20stories%20on%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20made%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%24630%2C000%20in%20sales%20in%20the%20first%20year%20selling%20only%20our%20supplement.%20By%20the%20second%20year%2C%20we%20had%20sales%20of%20%243%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Maxine%20Laceby%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655f37a14ca513d8242e067e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMaxine%20Laceby%20and%20her%20daughter%20and%20colleague%20Darcy.%20%3Cp%3EMaxine%20Laceby%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGradually%2C%20we%20brought%20on%20new%20people%20for%20finance%2C%20social%20media%2C%20and%20digital%20marketing.%20After%20a%20few%20years%20of%20keeping%20our%20heads%20down%20and%20working%20hard%2C%20we%20moved%20out%20of%20my%20garage%20and%20into%20a%20warehouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20we%20started%20looking%20for%20outside%20investment.%20I%20didn't%20want%20investors%20who%20offered%20the%20most%20money.%20I%20wanted%20investors%20who%20shared%20my%20business%20outlook%20and%20could%20look%20me%20in%20the%20eye%20when%20shit%20hit%20the%20fan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20investment%20was%20a%20turning%20point%20for%20our%20small%20business.%20We%20made%20%2434%20million%20in%20sales%20last%20year.%20Our%20team%20of%2067%20people%20works%20out%20of%20a%20warehouse%20triple%20the%20size%20of%20our%20first%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPeople%20don't%20underestimate%20me%20now%20I%20have%20experience%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWomen%20are%20underestimated%20in%20business%2C%20but%20the%20most%20underestimation%20comes%20from%20themselves.%20We're%20very%20humble%20and%20that's%20beautiful%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20do%20us%20any%20favors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226735%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Maxine%20Laceby%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655f37814ca513d8242e0672%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224490%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMaxine%20Laceby%20is%20now%20an%20award-winning%20entrepreneur.%20%3Cp%3EMaxine%20Laceby%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20no%20one%20took%20me%20seriously%20until%20I%20was%20turning%20over%20%2416%20million.%20Unfortunately%2C%20it's%20also%20true%20that%20only%202%25%20of%20funding%20in%20investment%20goes%20to%20females.%20It's%20not%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20I%20want%20to%20use%20my%20success%20to%20be%20there%20for%20other%20women.%20I'm%20part%20of%20a%20group%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbuywomenbuilt.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBuy%20Women%20Built%3C%2Fa