number%20and%20details%20of%20directions%2Forders%20issued%20by%20the%20government%20during%20the%20last%20five%20years%2C%20under%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act%2C%202000%20and%20Rules%20made%20thereunder%2C%20directing%20intermediaries%20and%20digital%20media%20to%20delete%2C%20modify%20or%20block%20any%20content%2C%20information%2C%20data%20or%20communication%20link.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20sought%20information%20year-wise%20and%20organisation-wise%3B%20and%20the%20number%20and%20details%20of%20directions%2Forders%20issued%20by%20the%20government%20during%20the%20last%20five%20years%20directing%20the%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20including%20Twitter%20and%20Facebook%2C%20to%20block%20or%20remove%20posts%2C%20entire%20accounts%2C%20or%20topic%20hashtags.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20the%20government%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20policies%20of%20the%20government%20are%20aimed%20at%20ensuring%20that%20the%20internet%20in%20India%20is%20open%2C%20safe%2C%20trusted%2C%20and%20accountable%20to%20all%20users.%20Accordingly%2C%20the%20government%20issues%20lawful%20directions%20for%20blocking%20access%20to%20information%20by%20the%20public%20under%20Section%2069A%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20(IT)%20Act%2C%202000%20which%20provides%20power%20to%20the%20government%20to%20issue%20such%20directions%20if%20it%20is%20necessary%20or%20expedient%20to%20do%20so%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%2C%20defence%20of%20India%2C%20security%20of%20the%20state%2C%20friendly%20relations%20with%20foreign%20States%20or%20public%20order%20or%20for%20inciting%20cognisable%20offence%20relating%20to%20above.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20blocked%20posts%20relate%20to%20X%20(13%2C660)%2C%20it%20is%20followed%20by%20Facebook%20(10%2C197)%2C%20YouTube%20(5%2C759)%2C%20Others%20(4%2C199)%2C%20and%20Instagram%20(3%2C023).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2