%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20portraits%20are%20captured%20through%20a%20lens%20which%20is%20at%20once%20revealing%2C%20sympathetic%20and%C2%A0Thadani%E2%80%99s%20work%20is%20troubling%20and%20captivating%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsha%20Thadani%2C%20nominated%20for%20the%20Henri%20Cartier-Bresson%20Award%20in%202015%2C%20is%20one%20of%20our%20most%20gifted%20artists.%20Her%20hope%20in%20this%20project%2C%20as%20she%20says%20in%20the%20opening%2C%20is%20%E2%80%99that%20it%20opens%20at%20least%20one%20door%20for%20a%20closed%20mind%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOften%20work%20that%20chooses%20to%20look%20away%20from%20the%20malls%2C%20the%20big%20weddings%20and%20the%20stock%20market%20and%20its%20billionaires.%20One%20is%20reminded%20of%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20memorable%20phrase%20in%20attacking%20Katharine%20Mayo%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3EMother%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%20This%20is%20not%20an%20accusation%20that%20can%20be%20levelled%20against%20the%20present%20work.%20It%20is%20searing%20and%20will%20leave%20an%20imprint%20on%20those%20who%20see%20it%20instantly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09123013%2FMYSELF.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09123013%2FMYSELF.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09123013%2FMYSELF-300x214.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09123013%2FMYSELF-1024x731.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688392%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22857%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAsha%20Thadani%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20what%20the%20artist%20achieves%20here%20by%C2%A0