3D%5C%22857%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20great%20Dr%20Babasaheb%20Ambedkar%20showed%20Indians%20the%20way%20to%20keep%20faith%20in%20the%20divine%20truth%20but%20reject%20the%20trappings%20of%20religion%20and%20dogma.%20The%20Navayan%20Buddhists%20walk%20in%20his%20footsteps.%20Photo%3A%20Asha%20Thadani%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Faakar-patel%5C%22%3EAakar%20Patel%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%20and%20columnist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702106140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09123245%2F10.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fbroken-photo-exhibition-asha-thadani%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Asha%20Thadani%20shows%20that%20though%20trapped%2C%20the%20individuals%20she%20introduces%20us%20to%20are%20not%20unaware%20of%20their%20shackles%20and%20give%20us%20a%20glimpse%20into%20their%20defiance%20and%20their%20spirit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fthe-arts%2Fbroken-photo-exhibition-asha-thadani%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Activist%20Nikhil%20Dey%20Among%20US%20Government%E2%80%99s%20International%20Anti-Corruption%20Champions%20for%202023%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F06%2FNikhil_Dey_youtube.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Indian%20social%20activist%20Nikhil%20Dey%20was%20among%2011%20persons%20that%20the%20US%20government%20recently%20recognised%20as%20International%20Anti-Corruption%20Champions%20for%202023%2C%20citing%20his%20decades-long%20work%20to%20build%20peasant%20and%20worker%20empowerment%20campaigns%20and%20exposing%20corruption%20in%20the%20delivery%20of%20government%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDey%20is%20the%20co-founder%20of%20Mazdoor%20Kisan%20Shakti%20Sangathan%20(MKSS)%2C%20which%20has%20led%20transparency%20and%20anti-corruption%20movements%20in%20India.%20The%20organisation%20is%20primarily%20based%20in%20Rajasthan%20that%20has%20led%20workers%E2%80%99%20and%20peasants%E2%80%99%20struggles%20for%20minimum%20wages%20and%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20on%20December%207%2C%20the%20US%20State%20Department%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Frecognizing-the-2023-anti-corruption-champions%2F%3Fs%3D31%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20past%2035%20years%2C%20activist%20Nikhil%20Dey%20has%20championed%20policy%20reforms%20to%20empower%20workers%20in%20India.%20He%20and%20his%20counterparts%20have%20brought%20to%20light%20official%20corruption%2C%20such%20as%20the%20underpayment%20of%20workers%20on%20official%20projects%2C%20and%20built%20peasant%20and%20worker%20empowerment%20campaigns%20targeting%20corruption%20in%20the%20delivery%20of%20government%20services.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20secretary%20of%20state%20Antony%20Blinken%20praised%C2%A0Dey%20for%20%E2%80%9Cworking%20with%20and%20for%20those%20harmed%20by%20corruption%2C%20and%20those%20particularly%20who%20are%20harmed%20most%20by%20it%3A%20underserved%2C%20marginalised%20populations%E2%80%9D.%20Blinken%20said%20Dey%20has%20helped%20communities%20in%20Rajasthan%20demand%20access%20to%20essential%20services%20and%20rights%20such%20as%20education%2C%20healthcare%2C%20fair%20wages%20and%20better%20working%20conditions.%20%E2%80%9CHis%20organization%20pioneered%20the%20practice%20of%20public%20audits%2C%20in%20which%20local%20officials%20have%20to%20report%20to%20communities%20how%20and%20where%20they%20spend%20the%20resources%2C%20and%20citizens%20have%20a%20chance%20themselves%20to%20ask%20probing%20questions%20of%20these%20officials%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20continued.%20These%20public%20audits%20spread%20across%20India%20and%20more%20citizens%20started%20taking%20the%20lead%20in%20holding%20officials%20to%20account%2C%20which%20%E2%80%9Cat%20its%20heart%2C%20is%20how%20democracy%20needs%20to%20work%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20award%2C%20set%20up%20in%202021%2C%20recognises%20the%20US%20government%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Csupport%20for%20anticorruption%20leaders%20who%20put%20their%20lives%20on%20the%20line%20to%20spur%20lasting%20change%E2%80%9D.%20Dey%20is%20the%20first%20Indian%20to%20receive%20the%20award.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2010%20other%20International%20Anti-Corruption%20Champions%20for%202023%20recognised%20by%20the%20US%20government%20on%20Thursday%20were%20Stanislau%20Ivashkevich%20of%20Belarus%2C%20Jean-Claude%20Mputu%20of%20the%20Democratic%20Republic%20of%20the%20Congo%2C%20Arturo%20Torres%20of%20Ecuador%2C%20Ali%20(Mukhammedali)%20Toktakunov%20of%20Kyrgyz%20Republic%2C%20Marc%20N.%20Kollie%20of%20Liberia%2C%20Veronica%20Mihailov-Moraru%20of%20Moldova%2C%20Vladimir%20Novovic%20of%20Montenegro%2C%20Annette%20Planells%20of%20Panama%2C%20Francisco%20Belo%20Simoes%20da%20Costa%20of%20Timor-Leste%2C%20and%20May%20De%20Silva%20of%20Seychelles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09114902%2FDIPNOTE-RESIZING-2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09114902%2FDIPNOTE-RESIZING-2.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09114902%2FDIPNOTE-RESIZING-2-300x150.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09114902%2FDIPNOTE-RESIZING-2-1024x512.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F09114902%2FDIPNOTE-RESIZING-2-800x400.png%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688385%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESecretary%20Antony%20J.%20Blinken%20takes%20a%20group%20photo%20with%20honorees%20at%20the%20Anti-Corruption%20Champions%20Award%20Ceremony%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20State%20in%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20December%207%2C%202023.%20Photo%3A%20US%20Government%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20Ambassador%20to%20India%20Eric%20Garcetti%20wrote%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%3A%20%E2%80%9CCongratulations%20to%20Nikhil%20Dey%2C%20a%20founding%20member%20of%20Mazdoor%20Kisan%20Shakti%20Sangathan%2C%20for%20being%20named%20an%20International%20Anti-Corruption%20Champion%20by%20the%20%40StateDept.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20United%20States%20stands%20with%20champions%20like%20Dey%20who%20work%20for%20transparency%2C%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20and%20justice%2C%E2%80%9D%20Garcetti%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlinken%20added%20that%20the%20State%20Department%20is%20committed%20to%20countering%20corruption%20and%20promoting%20integrity%20as%20a%20foreign%20policy%20priority%20and%20core%20national%20security%20interest.%20%E2%80%9COn%20the%20eve%20of%20International%20Anti-Corruption%20Day%2C%20December%209%2C%20the%20United%20States%20is%20proud%20to%20honour%20the%20individuals%20and%20institutions%20championing%20transparency%2C%20accountability%2C%20integrity%2C%20and%20good%20governance%20worldwide%2C%E2%80%9D%20Blinken%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.state.gov%2Fsecretary-antony-j-blinken-at-the-anti-corruption-champions-award-ceremony-2%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20Aruna%20Roy%20and%20Shankar%20Singh%2C%20Dey%E2%80%99s%20leadership%20of%20the%20MKSS%20saw%20the%20organisation%C2%A0play%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20the%20demand%2C%20formulation%20and%20implementation%20of%20both%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%20(RTI)%20and%20the%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act%20(NREGA).%20Dey%20is%20also%20involved%20in%20the%20right%20to%20food%20and%20right%20to%20work%20campaigns.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702102931000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F06%2FNikhil_Dey_youtube.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Factivist-nikhil-dey-us-government-international-anti-corruption-champion%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20co-founder%20of%20Mazdoor%20Kisan%20Shakti%20Sangathan%20was%20recognised%20for%20his%20decades-long%20work%20to%20build%20peasant%20and%20worker%20empowerment%20campaigns%20and%20exposing%20corruption%20in%20the%20delivery%20of%20government%20services.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Factivist-nikhil-dey-us-government-international-anti-corruption-champion%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Laura%20Kuenssberg%3A%20Ukraine%20in%20'mortal%20danger'%20without%20aid%2C%20Olena%20Zelenska%20warns%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702101291000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F169F0%2Fproduction%2F_131965629_045a4098.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67667035%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ukraine's%20first%20lady%20tells%20Sunday%20with%20Laura%20Kuenssberg%20that%20continued%20Western%20support%20is%20life%20or%20death.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1936%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67667035%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67667035.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67667035.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vikrant%20Will%20Soon%20Be%20Deployed%20Operationally%20but%20Navy%E2%80%99s%20Aircraft%20Carrier%20Dilemma%20To%20Continue%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F18142346%2FMig-29K_takeofff_from_INS_Vikrant.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChandigarh%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20INS%20Vikrant%2C%20the%20Indian%20Navy%E2%80%99s%20first%20indigenously%20designed%20aircraft%20carrier%20(IAC-1)%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20available%20imminently%20for%20operational%20deployment%2C%20some%2016%20months%20after%20its%20feverish%20commissioning%20in%20September%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVice%20Admiral%20M.A.%20Hampiholi%2C%20who%20heads%20the%20Southern%20Naval%20Command%2C%20told%20reporters%20in%20Kochi%20on%20December%203%20that%20Vikrant%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Coperationalised%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20end%20of%20January%202024%2C%20after%20completing%20its%20mandatory%20%E2%80%98guarantee%20refit%E2%80%99%20at%20Cochin%20Shipyard%20Limited%20(CSL)%2C%20where%20it%20was%20constructed.%20A%20%E2%80%98guarantee%20refit%E2%80%99%20is%20akin%20to%20the%20first%20service%20of%20a%20newly%20acquired%20vehicle%2C%20which%20entails%20repairing%2C%20re-equipping%2C%20and%20re-supplying%20the%20concerned%20platform%20to%20certify%20its%20overall%20functioning%20and%20operability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20so%2C%20the%20air%20arm%20of%20the%2040%2C000-tonne%20short-take-off%20barrier%20arrested%20recovery%20(STOBAR)%20power%20projection%20platform%20%E2%80%93%20comprising%2018%20Russian%20MiG-29K%2FKUB%20fighters%2C%20of%20a%20total%20of%20some%2030%20embarked%20aerial%20assets%20%E2%80%93%20inspired%20%E2%80%98limited%E2%80%99%20confidence.%20A%20cross-section%20of%20veteran%20Indian%20Navy%20aviators%20and%20industry%20officials%20said%20that%20since%20their%20induction%20in%202009%2C%20the%20navy%E2%80%99s%20entire%20MiG-29%20fleet%20had%20proven%20%E2%80%98inadequate%E2%80%99%20in%20meeting%20the%20operational%20requirements%20of%20forces%2C%20as%20they%20had%20demonstrated%20their%20inability%20to%20deliver%20their%20specified%20weapons%20payload%20to%20their%20stated%20ranges%20with%20a%20full%20fuel%20load%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20numerous%20other%20drawbacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20however%2C%20Vikrant%20is%20expected%20to%20operate%20the%20under-purchase%2026%20Dassault%20Rafale-M%20(Marine)%20multi-role%20carrier-borne%20fighters%20(MRCBF)%20from%20France%2C%20including%20eight%20twin-seat%20trainers.%20Negotiations%20to%20import%20these%20fighters%20for%20an%20estimated%20%246%20billion%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Findia-seeks-acquisition-of-26-rafale-marine-aircraft-from-france-2454710-2023-10-27%5C%22%3Eare%20ongoing%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20deal%20for%20them%2C%20according%20to%20Indian%20Navy%20officials%2C%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20inked%20by%20March%202024.%20Thereafter%2C%20fighter%20deliveries%20are%20expected%20to%20commence%2036%20months%20later%2C%20with%20the%20possibility%20of%20the%20French%20Navy%20even%20%E2%80%98loaning%E2%80%99%20some%20Rafale%20(M)%E2%80%99s%20to%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20in%20the%20interim%20to%20%E2%80%98familiarise%E2%80%99%20it%20with%20the%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20Indian%20Navy%20officials%20have%20iterated%20that%20the%20Rafale%20(M)s%20are%20being%20inducted%20as%20an%20%E2%80%98interim%E2%80%99%20measure%20and%2C%20in%20due%20course%2C%20would%20be%20supplemented%2C%20and%20eventually%20replaced%2C%20by%20the%20under-development%20indigenous%20twin-engine%20deck%20based%20fighter%20(TEDBF)%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20light%20combat%20aircraft%20(Navy).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Navy%20is%20optimistic%20that%20the%20prototype%20of%20the%20TEDBF%2C%20under%20development%20by%20the%20Aeronautical%20Development%20Agency%20and%20the%20public%20sector%20Hindustan%20Aeronautics%20Limited%2C%20would%20be%20ready%20by%202026%2C%20followed%20by%20its%20series%20production%202032%20onwards%2C%20but%20extended%20slippages%20remain%20endemic%20in%20all%20such%20ambitious%20domestic%20programmes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVikrant%E2%80%99s%20air%20arm%2C%20which%20also%20comprises%2012-odd%20rotary%20wing%20platforms%20like%20Russian%20Kamov%20Ka-31%20early%20warning%20and%20control%20(AEW%26amp%3BC)%20helicopters%20and%20the%20under-induction%20Lockheed%20Martin%2FSikorsky%20MH-60R%20multirole%20naval%20helicopters%20(MRHs)%2C%20in%20varying%20numbers%2C%20will%20be%20managed%20by%20the%20carriers%20Aviation%20Flight%20Complex%20(AFC)%20supplied%20by%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20Nevoske%20Design%20Bureau.%20The%20carrier%20air%20wings%E2%80%99s%20situational%20awareness%2C%20surveillance%20capability%20and%20capacity%20to%20track%20multiple%20aerial%20and%20surface%20targets%20will%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20be%20supported%20by%20the%20EL%2FM-2248%20MF-STAR%20(multi-functional%20digital%20active%20electronically%20scanned%20array%20radar)%20provided%20by%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20IAI-Elta.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20now%2C%20Vikrant%20has%20no%20alternative%20but%20to%20make%20do%20with%20MiG29K%2FKUBs%2C%2045%20of%20which%20were%20acquired%20by%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20between%202009%20and%202017%20for%20%242.29%20billion%2C%20but%20only%20around%2040%20of%20which%20were%20presently%20available%2C%20following%20losses%20in%20accidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202016%2C%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fmig-29k-planes-face-operation-deficiencies-cag%2Farticleshow%2F53400187.cms%5C%22%3Erigorously%20criticised%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20and%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20(MoD)%20for%20technically%20accepting%20the%20MiG-29K%2FKUB%20fighters%2C%20despite%20them%20being%20%E2%80%9Criddled%20with%20problems%2C%20discrepancies%2C%20and%20anomalies%E2%80%9D.%20In%20its%20damning%20audit%2C%20the%20CAG%20had%20revealed%20the%20fighters%E2%80%99%20multiple%20deficiencies%2C%20which%20included%20shortcomings%20with%20its%20airframe%2C%20its%20RD-33%20MK%20engines%20and%20fly-by-wire%20systems%3B%20in%20short%2C%20the%20entire%20fighter.%20The%20report%20also%20stated%20that%20the%20fighters%20had%20suffered%20repeated%20engine%20failures%2C%20with%20at%20least%2010%20cases%20of%20single-engine%20landings.%20Of%20the%2065%20RD-33MK%20turbofan%20engines%20received%20from%20their%20manufacturer%20Klimov%2C%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20had%20rejected%20or%20withdrawn%20at%20least%2040%20from%20service%20due%20to%20defects%2C%20the%20CAG%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20operational%20availability%20of%20the%20MiG-29Ks%20between%202014%20and%202016%20had%20fluctuated%20from%2015.93%25%20to%2037.63%25%2C%20while%20that%20of%20the%20MiG-29KUB%20dual-seat%20trainers%20was%20just%20between%2021.20%25%20and%2047.14%25%2C%20the%20CAG%20disclosed.%20It%20also%20revealed%20that%20these%20technical%20deficiencies%20would%20considerably%20reduce%20the%20MIG-29K%E2%80%99s%20overall%20service%20life%20of%206%2C000%20hours%20and%20that%20even%20its%20full-mission%20simulator%20had%20proven%20%E2%80%9Cunsuitable%E2%80%9D%20in%20training%20pilots%20for%20carrier%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20MiG-29K%2FKUB%20fleet%20continued%20to%20face%20severe%20maintenance%20problems%2C%20as%20a%20large%20number%20needed%20repair%20after%20each%20deck%20landing%20that%20damaged%20many%20of%20the%20fighters%E2%80%99%20on-board%20components.%20There%20were%20also%20complaints%20from%20the%20Indian%20Navy%20regarding%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20inability%20to%20incorporate%20all%20agreed-upon%20features%20into%20the%20MiG-29Ks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20state%20of%20affairs%20had%20resulted%20from%20the%202014%20sanctions%2C%20still%20in%20place%2C%20imposed%20on%20Russia%20by%20the%20US%2C%20European%20Union%20states%20and%20other%20international%20organisations%20for%20its%20military%20intervention%20in%20Crimea%2C%20all%20of%20which%20prevented%20Moscow%20from%20providing%20several%20of%20the%20MiG-29%2FK%E2%80%99KUBs%20components.%20This%20situation%20had%20only%20deteriorated%20over%20the%20past%2022%20months%20following%20additional%20embargoes%20imposed%20on%20Russia%20for%20its%20ongoing%20assault%20on%20%C2%A0Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20seven%20years%20after%20the%20excoriating%20CAG%20report%2C%20little%20had%20changed%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20MiG-29K%2FKUBs%20operational%20efficacy.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20inefficiency%20of%20the%20MiG-29k%2FKUBs%20was%20well%20known%20to%20the%20MoD%20and%20the%20IN%20for%20years%2C%20but%20for%20inexplicable%20reasons%20they%20failed%20to%20acquire%20a%20substitute%20platform%20to%20coincide%20with%20Vikrant%E2%80%99s%20commissioning%E2%80%9D%20said%20Amit%20Cowshish%2C%20former%20MoD%20acquisitions%20advisor.%20This%20avoidable%20lapse%20had%20adversely%20impacted%20the%20navy%E2%80%99s%20operational%20timetable%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20headway%20on%20Navy%E2%80%99s%20third%20carrier%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20IN%20was%20continuing%20to%20grapple%20with%20securing%20MoD%20approval%20for%20a%20third%20carrier%2C%20designed%20and%20built%20indigenously%20to%20supplement%20Vikrant%20and%20INS%20Vikramaditya%20(ex-Admiral%20Gorshkov)%2C%20the%2046%2C000-tonne%20refurbished%20Russian%20Kiev-class%20platform%20commissioned%20into%20the%20IN%20in%202013.%20News%20reports%2C%20quoting%20senior%20IN%20officials%20had%20stated%20that%20the%20MoD%E2%80%99s%20Defence%20Acquisition%20Council%20was%20likely%20to%20approve%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20proposed%20carrier-a%20follow-on%20to%20the%20Vikrant-at%20its%20meeting%20in%20early%20December.%20But%20for%20reasons%20unknown%2C%20this%20did%20not%20occur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20years%2C%20successive%20IN%20Chiefs%20of%20Staff%20had%20argued%20and%20lobbied%20hard%20for%20a%20third%20carrier%20%E2%80%93%20one%20for%20each%20seaboard%20and%20one%20in%20reserve%20%E2%80%93%20and%20in%202015%20the%20MoD%20had%20even%20sanctioned%20Rs30%20crore%20to%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Naval%20Design%20in%20New%20Delhi%20to%20begin%20conceptualising%20plans%20for%20a%2065%2C000-tonne%20IAC-2%2C%20but%20little%20came%20of%20that%20endeavour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F29133209%2F2022_8img26_Aug_2022_PTI08_26_2022_000172B.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F29133209%2F2022_8img26_Aug_2022_PTI08_26_2022_000172B.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F29133209%2F2022_8img26_Aug_2022_PTI08_26_2022_000172B-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F29133209%2F2022_8img26_Aug_2022_PTI08_26_2022_000172B-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-616435%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIn%20this%20undated%20file%20photo%2C%20the%20Indigenous%20Aircraft%20Carrier%20(IAC)%20Vikrant%20sails%20in%20the%20sea.%20Photo%3A%20Handout%20via%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20in%20recent%20months%20IN%20officials%20confirmed%20that%20due%20to%20a%20financial%20resource%20crunch%2C%20the%20force%20had%20settled%20on%20building%20a%2040%2C000-tonne%20flattop%2C%20analogous%20to%20Vikrant%2C%20principally%20to%20ensure%20that%20CSL%E2%80%99s%20skills%20in%20carrier%20construction%2C%20developed%20at%20great%20expense%20and%20over%20an%20extended%20period%2C%20did%20not%20dissipate.%20But%20alongside%20many%20navalists%20also%20questioned%20the%20operational%20efficacy%20of%20constructing%20another%20less-capable%20%E2%80%98lightweight%E2%80%99%20carrier%2C%20which%20they%20said%20would%20be%20forced%20to%20operate%20within%20the%20engagement%20envelope%20of%20its%20enemy%E2%80%99s%20shore-based%20missiles%20and%20air%20defence%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERetired%20Commander%20Abhijit%20Singh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fopinion%2Ffor-navy-small-aircraft-carriers-limit-options-101701696045571.html%5C%22%3Econtended%20recently%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20IN%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20opt%20for%20a%20smaller%20carrier%2C%20which%20was%20a%20%E2%80%98valuable%E2%80%99%20asset%20in%20peacetime%20activities%2C%20stemmed%20from%20diminishing%20financial%20options.%20Yet%2C%20policymakers%20ought%20to%20know%2C%20he%20cautioned%2C%20that%20a%20small%20aircraft%20carrier%20will%20%E2%80%98not%20cut%20it%20in%20combat%20with%20a%20worthy%20adversary%20in%20the%20littorals.%20Moreover%2C%20with%20its%20two%2060%2C000%20and%2080%2C000-tonne%20carriers%2C%20China%20was%20unlikely%20to%20be%20deterred%20by%20the%20presence%20of%20a%2040%2C000-tonne%20Indian%20flat-top%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20Region%20(IOR)%2C%20added%20the%20analyst%20from%20the%20Observer%20Research%20Foundation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20debate%20over%20the%20proposed%20IAC-2%20has%20been%20long%20and%20tortuous%2C%20plagued%20not%20only%20by%20its%20astronomical%20cost%2C%20but%20also%20its%20overall%20operational%20efficacy%20in%20an%20environment%20of%20burgeoning%20anti-access%2Farea%20denial%20(A2%2FAD)%20capability%20via%20long-range%20ballistic%20and%20cruise%20missiles.%20Steadily%20declining%20domestic%20military%20budgets%20and%20vacillation%20by%20the%20MoD%20in%20approving%20the%20programme%2C%20too%20had%20collectively%20thwarted%20the%20carrier%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0Nonetheless%2C%20even%20within%20the%20navy%2C%20senior%20officers%20question%20the%20monetary%20logic%20of%20building%20a%20new%20carrier%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20inducting%20additional%20diesel-electric%20submarines%20(SSKs)%20%E2%80%93%20whose%20numbers%20presently%20equalled%2016.%20And%2C%20of%20these%2C%20seven%20were%20Russian%20Type%20877%20EKM%20%E2%80%98Kilo%E2%80%99%20class%20variants%20and%20four%20were%20German-origin%20HDW%20Type%20209%2F1500%20boats%2C%20all%20between%2020%20and%2034%20years%20old%2C%20with%20several%20of%20them%20due%20either%20for%20retirement%2C%20or%20in%20limited%20instances%2C%20upgrade.%20The%20remaining%20five%20SSKs%20were%20licence-built%20French%20Kalvari%20(Scorpene)%20class%20boats%2C%20with%20a%20sixth%20scheduled%20for%20commissioning%20in%20early%202024%2C%20taking%20thereby%20the%20total%20number%20of%20such%20boats%20to%2017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20SSK%20numbers%20were%20seven%20boats%20less%20than%20the%2024%20submarines%20that%20the%20navy%20was%20projected%20to%20operate%20by%202030%20in%20accordance%20with%20its%20Maritime%20Capability%20Perspective%20Plan%20(MCPP).%20Correspondingly%2C%20equally%20critical%20surface%20combatants%20like%20corvettes%2C%20mine-sweepers%2C%20destroyers%20and%20frigates%20were%20in%20short%20supply%2C%20as%20were%20naval%20utility%20helicopters%20and%20unmanned%20aerial%20vehicles%20(UAVs)%20and%20other%20assorted%20missiles%20and%20ordnance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20and%20China%E2%80%99s%20naval%20prowess%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAircraft%20carrier%20operations%20represent%20the%20apex%20of%20flexible%20naval%20power%20projection%2C%20and%20nuclear%20rivals%20China%20and%20India%20have%20placed%20these%20platforms%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20their%20maritime%20force%20development%20plans%20in%20their%20respective%20strategies%20of%20%E2%80%98dominating%E2%80%99%20the%20strategic%20IOR.%20By%20comparison%2C%20China%20is%20relatively%20new%20to%20carrier%20operations%2C%20having%20had%20to%20start%20from%20scratch%20in%20the%20mid-1980s%20with%20neither%20naval%20aircraft%2C%20vessel%2C%20training%20pipeline%2C%20or%20operational%20experience%20to%20build%20upon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStarting%20in%201985%2C%20China%20began%20by%20acquiring%20four%20retired%20carriers%20to%20analyse%20and%20study%20in%20its%20quest%20to%20launch%20such%20platforms%20for%20the%20Peoples%20Liberation%20Army%20Navy%20(PLAN)%3A%20the%20British-built%20HMAS%20Melbourne%20from%20Australia%20and%20three%20ex-Soviet%20carriers%2C%20Minsk%2C%20Kiev%20and%20Varyag.%20The%20last%20named%20underwent%20an%20extensive%20refit%2C%20to%20emerge%20as%20the%20Liaoning%2C%20the%20PLAN%E2%80%99s%20first%20operational%20carrier%20with%2040%20embarked%20fighters%20and%20helicopters%20and%20one%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20served%20as%20a%20basis%20for%20China%E2%80%99s%20subsequent%20design%20iterations%20for%20similar%20platforms.%20Presently%2C%20other%20than%20Varyag%2C%20the%20PLAN%20operates%20the%20follow-on%20Shandong%20and%20Fujian%2C%20which%20is%20being%20kitted%20out.%20Naval%20analysts%20anticipate%20China%20operating%20a%20total%20of%20five%20or%20six%20such%20carriers%20by%202030%2C%20each%20one%20an%20improvement%20on%20the%20previous%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20began%20operating%20carriers%20in%201961%2C%20with%20INS%20Vikrant%20(ex-HMS%20Hercules)%20a%2016%2C000-tonne%20Majestic-class%20carrier%20followed%20by%20INS%20Virat%20(ex-HMS%20Hermes)%2C%20a%2023%2C900-tonne%20Centaur-class%20platform%20with%20vertical-take-off-and-landing%20(VTOL)%20Sea%20Harrier%20fighters%20that%20were%20retired%20in%20early%202017.%20IN%20officials%20maintain%20that%20the%20forces%20%E2%80%98institutional%E2%80%99%20maturity%2C%20experience%2C%20and%20knowledge%20provide%20it%20with%20a%20decisive%20operational%20edge%20over%20rival%20navies%2C%20including%20China%E2%80%99s.%20The%20IN%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20few%20navies%20to%20have%20operated%20CATOBAR%20%5Bcatapult-assisted%20takeoff%20barrier%20arrested%20recovery%5D%2C%20VTOL%20and%20STOBAR%20platforms%2C%20which%20not%20only%20gives%20it%20higher%20aviation%20skills%20but%20also%20advanced%20carrier%20tactics%2C%20techniques%20and%20procedures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20officers%20cautioned%20against%20such%20assertiveness%2C%20arguing%20that%20past%20performance%20was%20no%20guarantee%20of%20future%20success.%20They%20advised%20that%20it%20would%20be%20a%20grave%20error%20to%20underestimate%20the%20PLAN%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20telescope%20the%20basics%20of%20carrier%20aviation%20within%20a%20shorter%20timescale%2C%20and%20counselled%20the%20IN%20to%20adopt%20a%20more%20pragmatic%20and%20rational%20approach%20to%20capability%20building%2C%20shorn%20of%20the%20hard-sell.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702099471000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F18142346%2FMig-29K_takeofff_from_INS_Vikrant.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fvikrant-indian-navy-aircraft-carrier-dilemma%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20air%20arm%20of%20the%20indigenous%20carrier%20only%20inspires%20'limited%20confidence'%2C%20according%20to%20experts.%20The%20navy%20also%20continues%20to%20grapple%20with%20securing%20approval%20for%20a%20third%20carrier%20to%20supplement%20Vikrant%20and%20INS%20Vikramaditya.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fvikrant-indian-navy-aircraft-carrier-dilemma%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israel-Hamas%20War%3A%20US%20Vetoes%20UN%20Security%20Council%20Resolution%20for%20Gaza%20Ceasefire%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16121246%2Fimage1170x530cropped-1-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EA%20UN%20Security%20Council%20resolution%20calling%20for%20an%20immediate%20cease-fire%20in%20Gaza%20failed%20after%20the%20United%20States%2C%20a%20veto-wielding%20permanent%20member%20of%20the%20Council%2C%20voted%20against%20the%20measure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20US%20engaged%20in%20good%20faith%20on%20this%20text%2C%E2%80%9D%20US%20Deputy%20Envoy%20to%20the%20UN%20Robert%20Wood%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20resolution%20was%20%E2%80%9Cdivorced%20from%20reality%E2%80%9D%20and%20would%20not%20change%20the%20situation%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20Gaza.%20Wood%20said%20the%20text%20did%20not%20include%20language%20condemning%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20terror%20attacks%20on%20Israel%20on%20October%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20an%20immediate%20cease-fire%20now%20would%20keep%20Hamas%20in%20place%20and%20allow%20it%20to%20carry%20out%20more%20terror%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIsrael%2C%20Hamas%20react%20to%20resolution%E2%80%99s%20failure%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fisrael%2Ft-19067044%5C%22%3EIsrael%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98s%20foreign%20minister%20Eli%20Cohen%20thanked%20the%20US%20for%20its%20vote%20against%20a%20resolution%20calling%20for%20a%20humanitarian%20cease-fire%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20gratitude%20to%20our%20ally%2C%20the%20US%2C%20for%20its%20support%20to%20continue%20the%20fight%20to%20bring%20the%20hostages%20home%20and%20to%20eliminate%20the%20Hamas%20terrorist%20organisation%2C%20which%20will%20bring%20a%20better%20future%20to%20the%20region%2C%E2%80%9D%20Cohen%20wrote%20on%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20cease-fire%20at%20this%20time%20would%20prevent%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Hamas%20terrorist%20organisation%2C%20which%20is%20committing%20war%20crimes%20and%20crimes%20against%20humanity%2C%20and%20would%20enable%20it%20to%20continue%20ruling%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20senior%20Hamas%20official%20Izzat%20al-Rishq%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20the%20group%2C%20designated%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20by%20the%20US%20and%20others%2C%20strongly%20condemned%20the%20US%20veto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20US%20obstruction%20of%20the%20issuance%20of%20a%20cease-fire%20resolution%20is%20a%20direct%20participation%20with%20%5BIsrael%5D%C2%A0in%20killing%20our%20people%20and%20committing%20more%20massacres%20and%20ethnic%20cleansing%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECohen%20again%20criticised%20UN%20Secretary-General%20Antonio%20Guterres%20and%20his%20decision%20to%20invoke%20Article%2099%20of%20the%20UN%20Charter%20and%20formally%20warn%20the%20Security%20Council%20of%20a%20global%20threat%20from%20the%20war.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fisrael-hamas-war-live-blog-dec-6%2Flive-67643127%5C%22%3EThat%20decision%20led%20to%20Friday%E2%80%99s%20session%20and%20vote%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGuterres%E2%80%99%20appeal%20to%20stand%20on%20the%20side%20of%20Hamas%20and%20request%20a%20cease-fire%20disgraces%20his%20position%2C%E2%80%9D%20Cohen%20said.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20invocation%20of%20Article%2099%2C%20after%20it%20was%20not%20used%20for%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20or%20for%20the%20civil%20war%20in%20Syria%2C%20is%20another%20example%20of%20Guterres%E2%80%99%20biased%20and%20one-sided%20stance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fisrael-hamas-war-us-vetoes-un-call-for-gaza-cease-fire%2Flive-67663645%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20originally%20published%20on%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftop-stories%2Fs-9097%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flogs1279.xiti.com%2Fhit.xiti%3Fs%3D531599%26s2%3D2%26p%3Dthewire.in%3A%3AVolltexte%3A%3Athewire.in_Volltexte_JS%26di%3D%26an%3D%26ac%3D%26x1%3D1%26x2%3D2%26x5%3Dthewire.in_Volltexte_JS%26x6%3D1%26x8%3Den-VAS-Volltexte-JavaScript-thewire.in-dwde%26x10%3Dthewire.in%3A%3AVolltexte%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702097023000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16121246%2Fimage1170x530cropped-1-1.jpg%2